wiki.summary: Who is a solo single by Jimin a member of the South Korean boy group BTS, released on July 19, 2024, as part of his solo album "MUSE." The song is an R&B-pop track with electronic and hip-hop elements. “Who" was produced by Pdogg, GHSTLOOP, Jon Bellion, Pete Nappi, and Tenroc. The lyrics, written by GHSTLOOP, Jason Cornet, Jon Bellion, Pete Nappi and Pdogg, The song explores the incessant and almost desperate search for an idealized love, someone he has not yet found, but who constantly occupies his thoughts and dreams. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: Who is a solo single by Jimin a member of the South Korean boy group BTS, released on July 19, 2024, as part of his solo album "MUSE." The song is an R&B-pop track with electronic and hip-hop elements. “Who" was produced by Pdogg, GHSTLOOP, Jon Bellion, Pete Nappi, and Tenroc. The lyrics, written by GHSTLOOP, Jason Cornet, Jon Bellion, Pete Nappi and Pdogg, The song explores the incessant and almost desperate search for an idealized love, someone he has not yet found, but who constantly occupies his thoughts and dreams. Chart Performance "Who" achieved remarkable success globally: 1. US Billboard Hot 100: Peaked at number 12. 2. UK Singles Chart: Reached number 4. 3. Spotify Global: Peaked at number 1. 4. UK Official Singles Sales Chart: Topped the Chart. 5. Billboard Global 200: Debuted at 1. 6. Spotify US: Peaked at number 1. Sales and Certifications 1.
